# bat auto-detects the terminal's light/dark background and picks the matching
# OKSolar theme. This also fixes paru's PKGBUILD/LICENSE review, which pipes
# through bat. Override for one call with `bat --theme="OKSolar Sky" ...`.
#
# `auto:always` forces the terminal-background query even when bat's output is
# redirected/piped (e.g. paru captures bat and shows it in less) — without it,
# bat can't detect light/dark in a pipe and falls back to the dark theme.
--theme="auto:always"
--theme-dark="OKSolar Dark"
--theme-light="OKSolar Light"
